{
  "texts": [
    "(33) is the influence functions' estimate of the leave-one-out influence of z i on z te.",
    "Calculating inverse Hessian (H (T)) -1 directly requires O(np 2 + p 3) time and O(p 2) space (Koh & Liang, 2017).",
    "For large models, this is clearly prohibitive.",
    "Rather than computing (H (T)) -1 directly, Koh & Liang (2017) instead estimate Hessian-vector prod- uct (HVP) with each training instance's pointwise influence then Koh & Liang (2017) use the stochastic algorithm of Pearlmutter (1994) and Agarwal et al. (2017) to estimate s test.",
    "This reduces influence functions' complexity to just O(np) time and O(n + p) space."
  ]
}